{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μόχθ-ος</b>, ὁ, <br /> = Homeric μόγος, <b>toil, hardship, distress</b>, ἀμφὶ δ᾽ ἀέθλῳ δῆριν ἔχειν καὶ μ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 306 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μόχθων ἀμπνοά, ἀμοιβά, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 8.7, “N.” 5.48: frequently in Trag., 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 921, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 480, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also in <i>plural</i>, <b>toils, troubles, hardships</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 541 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], etc.; of the <b>labours</b> of Heracles, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1101, 1170 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. τέκνων <b>for</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1261 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μόχθον ἀμφὶ πράγμασι epigram cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.184 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Ἀπελλείου μ. γραφίδος, of a picture, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “APl.” 4.178 (Antip. Sid.).—Rare in early Prose (not in 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus or Oratt.), compare μ. καὶ ταλαιπωρίη 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 223; ἐλευθέριοι μ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 2.4; διὰ μόχθων [prev. author] “Cyr.” 1.6.25: frequently in LXX, LXX.Exo.18.8, +others; κόπος καὶ μ. NT.1Thes.2.9 \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; μ. implies <b>hardship</b>, πόνος <b>work</b> (but μ. is said to be Cretan dialect for πόνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anecdota Graeca - Bekker” 1096). \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G3449","accentedUnicode":"μόχθος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3425","matchingForm":"μόγις","stepTransliteration":"mogis","gloss":"hardly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"硬不","_es_Gloss":"apenas","_zh_Gloss":"硬不"}],"shortDe